GriefShare groups meet weekly to help you face these challenges and move toward rebuilding your life. Join us  on Wednesdays at 6:00 p.m. Room 502 . Please use the north glass doors to enter building.

title: Collective NIGHTS (Millersburg Campus)
description: High school students! Please plan to join us for our high school only environment, Collective NIGHTS. Join us for worship, relevant messages, and other unpredictable elements. Don't miss out! Bring a friend with you on Wednesday nights from 6 - 8 p.m.  Will meet in the Collective.

title: DivorceCare Support Group (Dover Campus)
description: Most people will tell you that separation and divorce are the most painful and stressful experiences they’ve ever faced. It’s a confusing time when you feel isolated and have lots of questions about issues you’ve never faced before. DivorceCare groups  meet weekly to help you face these challenges and move toward rebuilding your life.

title: DOV CG DC4K
description: DC4K is a special group to help your children heal from the pain caused by a separation or divorce. DC4K provides your children with a safe and neutral place to recognize and learn to share their feelings. For 13 weeks your children become involved in  a fun, caring group at NewPointe. The weekly session topics help your children learn that God's love strengthens them and helps them turn their sadness to hope and their anger to joy. DC4K is a powerful ministry for kids 5-12 years of age

title: Develop Spiritual Habits Campus Group (Millersburg Campus)
description: Do you know there are some spiritual habits that will enable you to become more like Jesus? Together, through teaching and discussion we'll explore an overview of the four basic spiritual habits every Christian needs in order to grow in their faith: daily  time in God's word, prayer, tithing, and fellowship. Adult Meeting Room

title: Discover Influence in Your World (Wooster Campus)
description: Influence in Your World: While we believe a person’s faith is deeply personal, it was never meant to be private. Jesus, before He left the earth, told His followers to go out and make a difference in the world. This Discover Group will help you learn how  you can live your life in a way that makes an impactful and lasting difference in the world. Group meets in the Lower Adult Meeting Room

title: How To Share Your Faith Campus Group (Dover Campus)
description: Did you know that introducing people to Jesus Christ doesn’t have to be intimidating or frustrating? With just a little direction and encouragement, communicating our faith in Christ can be the most natural thing in the world. Join us as we explore how  to become effective communicators of God’s life-changing message. Together through teaching and discussion we’ll consider how to engage people in spiritual conversations and point them toward faith in God. Meet in the Velocity Theater.

title: Couples Campus Group (Canton Campus)
description: This campus group will help strengthen your marriage by helping you learn to put God first. We will talk about communication skills, understanding expectations, boundaries, etc. We believe if a couple keeps God first in their marriage and they focus on  being Christ-Like, there will be less conflict and more understanding. Meeting in the Café

title: Discover Intimacy with God (Akron Campus)
description: Our Heavenly Father desires to have an intimate relationship with us, a relationship in which we can be fully known with no fear of rejection. God's intimacy with man was destroyed when sin, sorrow, and death entered the world. And God has been striving  to reconcile the relationship ever since. Join us at the Gateway Conference Center for this campus group as we explore the obstacles that hinder intimacy with God and how to remove them.

title: Mentor Mondays  (Canton Campus)
description: Mentoring is NewPointe's way of caring for people going through hardships in life.
